In a small bowl, combine soup and milk; set aside. In a medium bowl, combine tuna, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheddar cheese half of the onions and 3/4 cup of the soup mixture; mix well. Divide mixture among tortillas and roll up. Place, seam side down, in a greased 12-in. x 8-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle with tomatoes if desired. Cover and bake at 350 degrees F for 35 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions. Return to the oven for 5 minutes.